There&#39;re many ways!

----------

Using `@ResponseBody`:

    @ResponseBody
    @ExceptionHandler(EntityNotFoundException.class)
    protected ProblemDetail handleEntityNotFoundException(EntityNotFoundException ex, 
                                                          HttpServletRequest request) {
        ProblemDetail problemDetail = forStatusAndDetail(NOT_FOUND, ex.getMessage());
        problemDetail.setTitle(&quot;entity.not.found&quot;);
        return problemDetail;
    }

----------

With Spring `ResponseEntity` `static` mode:

    @ExceptionHandler(EntityNotFoundException.class)
    protected ResponseEntity&lt;ProblemDetail&gt; handleEntityNotFoundException(
            EntityNotFoundException ex, 
            HttpServletRequest request) {
        ProblemDetail problemDetail = forStatusAndDetail(NOT_FOUND, ex.getMessage());
        problemDetail.setTitle(&quot;entity.not.found&quot;);
        return ResponseEntity.ok(problemDetail);
    }

Others status supported:

    accepted()
    badRequest()
    noContent()
    notFound()
    unprocessableEntity()


----------

Example with custom `body` and `header`:

    @GetMapping(&quot;/customHeader&quot;)
    ResponseEntity&lt;String&gt; customHeader() {
        return ResponseEntity.ok()
            .header(&quot;Custom-Header&quot;, &quot;app-custom-header&quot;)
            .body(&quot;Application custom body content&quot;);
    }

----------

Or with traditional constructor and custom status:

    return new ResponseEntity&lt;&gt;(body, HttpStatus.OK);

----------

### Reference:

 - https://www.baeldung.com/spring-response-entity
 - https://www.baeldung.com/spring-request-response-body
 - https://docs.spring.io/spring-framework/docs/current/javadoc-api/org/springframework/http/ResponseEntity.html

